## Decisions Made
- Two-tier state: verb mode for data-plane, SM for control-plane — eliminates ~22 SM roundtrip turns per session
- Patch/verb over file-split: peer review recommended verb field whitelists instead of per-field file separation
- Fate-sharing for batch candidates: validation failure demotes ALL WIs atomically, no partial recovery
- Pre-WAL dependency computation: resolved before WAL write to ensure replay determinism
- Complexity default null instead of "simple": forces Architect to explicitly assess every WI
- Verify hard gate at BUILD_PLAN→IMPLEMENT boundary: prevents empty-verify WIs from entering implementation

## Problems Encountered
- Context compaction mid-implementation: session ran out of context after Step 5, resumed via cold summary. No state lost — all edits persisted on disk.
- Existing test fixtures used old `active_candidate`/`candidate_activated_at` fields: updated all test fixtures to use `active_candidate_set`/`candidate_queue`.

## Constraints Identified
- Verb whitelist must be hardcoded: adding new verbs requires code change to state-commit, not configuration
- Fast-track is per-batch conservative: ALL WIs in a set must meet all 4 conditions
- depends_on is immutable after initial upsert: prevents dependency drift since Agent Teams API lacks `removeBlockedBy`

## Open Questions
- None — all design decisions were resolved during peer review phase

